  "text": "The Gemara explains that <b>this is what Rabban Gamliel said to his sons: Even according to the Rabbis, who say</b> that the mitzva may be performed only <b>until midnight,</b> the biblical obligation to perform <b>the mitzva</b> continues <b>until dawn, and that which they say</b> that it may only be recited <b>until midnight</b> is <b>in order to distance a person from transgression.</b>",
